The paper discusses machine learning techniques for matching objects in two heterogeneous domains, which is a common problem in several sub-fields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on feature-based matrix factorization and proposes a novel parallel and efficient algorithm for the task. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions handling large datasets, which suggests the possibility of using techniques from cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) to optimize the algorithm.
